'''Boelo''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] who served in the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt's]] [[Jabba's criminal empire/Legends|criminal empire]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. For a [[Time/Legends|time]], he served as Jabba's right-hand man, before eventually being replaced by [[Naroon Cuthus]] several [[Standard year/Legends|years]] before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], Boelo visited [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]], and shortly afterward accompanied Jabba to [[Docking Bay 94/Legends|Docking Bay 94]] in Tatooine's [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]], where the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] spoke to [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] over a debt the latter owed Jabba.

==Biography==
[[File:Boelo_SWANH_SE_1.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Boelo in Docking Bay 94]]
The [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="ANH" /> Boelo<ref name="CCG" /> lived<ref name="ANH" /> during the early years<ref name="The Essential Guide to Warfare">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref> of [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], a conflict between the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. At some point, he joined the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt's]] [[Jabba's criminal empire/Legends|criminal empire]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]],<ref name="ANH" /> becoming the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] right-hand man, and was eventually replaced in that position by [[Naroon Cuthus]]. He also owned a pet [[Womp rat/Legends|womp rat]] named [[Worra]].<ref name="CCG" />

In 0 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]],<ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> Boelo was present at the bar of [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]] within Tatooine's [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] when a [[Moisture farmer/Legends|farmboy]] named [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and a [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] named [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] arrived, looking for a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] to take them and the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] to the planet [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]], ultimately meeting [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]. Boelo later accompanied Jabba on a visit to [[Docking Bay 94/Legends|Docking Bay 94]] in the spaceport. He stood near the [[Entry ramp/Legends|entry ramp]] of Solo's [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]] [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] when Jabba intended to collect a debt Solo owed the crime lord. After Solo arrived and made a deal with Jabba, the Hutt and his entourage, including Boelo, left the site.<ref name="ANH" />

==Personality and traits==
Boelo would see what he wanted to see, and hear what he wanted to hear.<ref name="CCG" /> He had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and fair skin.<ref name="ANH" /> He also possessed a certain level of [[Force-attunement]].<ref name="CCG" />

==Equipment==
Boelo sported a [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]], and carried an ammunition [[Bandolier/Legends|bandolier]] across his trench coat.<ref name="ANH" />

==Behind the scenes==
Boelo first appeared as an uncredited extra in the [[1977]] film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], as a patron extra in the Mos Eisley [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] scene. He was also in a scene cut from the film, among Jabba's henchmen confronting Han Solo later on in the spaceport. The scene would be added into the film's [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Edition]], released in [[1997]].<ref name="ANH" /> One year later, in [[1998]], Boelo was first named, and given a brief backstory, on a card for the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]]{{'s}} ''[[Special Edition Limited]]'' expansion set.<ref name="CCG" />

